## 14. Worked example: order-of-element table for (ℤ/15)×

The multiplicative group `(ℤ/15)× = {1, 2, 4, 7, 8, 11, 13, 14}` has `φ(15) = 8` elements. Let's compute the order of each.

```scheme
(define n 15)
(define Z15 (alg/zn n))
(define units (alg/zn-units n))

(define order-table
  (map (lambda (a)
         (list a (alg/element-order Z15 a)))
       units))

order-table
```
[VISUAL: prints pairs `(element order)` for all 8 units]
<!-- BUILD: run and render as a table with two columns: element, order -->

Expected orders divide `4` (the exponent of the group; `(ℤ/15)× ≅ ℤ/2 × ℤ/4`).

---

### 14.1 Checking the structure

The group `(ℤ/15)×` is not cyclic (no element of order `8`). It's isomorphic to `ℤ/2 × ℤ/4`.

```scheme
(define max-order
  (apply max (map cadr order-table)))

max-order
```
[VISUAL: prints `4` — the largest order, confirming non-cyclicity]
<!-- BUILD: run and verify group structure -->

