## 16. Final summit artifact: polynomial factorization + order table

Combine symbolic and numeric algebra: factor a polynomial, compute the order table of a group.

```scheme
(define poly (sym/poly 'x (list -15 1 1)))

(define factors-poly (sym/factor poly))

(define n 15)
(define Z15 (alg/zn n))
(define units (alg/zn-units n))

(define order-table
  (map (lambda (a)
         (list a (alg/element-order Z15 a)))
       units))

(list factors-poly order-table)
```
[VISUAL: prints the factored polynomial and the order table; render as two side-by-side panels or sequentially]
<!-- BUILD: run and display both artifacts — factorization as symbolic expression, order table as grid -->

The polynomial `x² + x - 15` and the group `(ℤ/15)×` are both algebraic structures we can factor and analyze. The summit: a single program that does both.

